Business Brief -- Singer Sewing Co.:
   Firm Says Some Operations
   Will Be Moved to the U.S.
"We hope that by putting production back into this
country, it will lead to stable pricing and reliable
delivery," said a spokesman, who added that North Carolina
has a large supply of skilled workers. "It's a good thing to
bring appliances back to these shores."
   The spokesman said the company hadn't yet decided which
items will be manufactured at the North Carolina operations.
Its small appliances include blenders, coffee makers, irons
and other items.